msgid "Description: this is the name that will appear in the drop-down menu when creating a new serial subscription; make sure it is descriptive"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/serials.rst:48
msgid "Unit: this is the unit used for counting the cycle of publication. Choose either none (for irregular frequencies), day, week, month, or year."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/serials.rst:51
msgid "Issues per unit: this is how many issues are published during the unit chosen above (this will usually be 1)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/serials.rst:54
msgid "Units per issue: this is how many units must we count until the next issue is published."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/serials.rst:57 ../../source/serials.rst:159
msgid "Display order: this is the display order in the drop-down menu when :ref:`creating a new subscription<add-a-subscription-label>` (you may want to put the most used frequencies at the top and the less frequent at the bottom; the top-most position is 0). Several frequencies can have the same display order value. If this is the case, they will appear in the order they were created."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/serials.rst:66
msgid "To understand 'issues per unit' versus 'units per issue' you can read it as '<*issues* per unit> issue(s) every <*units* per issues> <unit>'. For example, a biweekly frenquency (every two weeks) would be '1 issue every 2 weeks'. So 'issues per unit' would be 1 and 'units per issue' would be 2. See below for more examples."
msgstr ""

